The chances of having a heart attack, the number one killer in the United States, have 
decreased significantly in the last decade. Leading the fight against heart disease are the 
new calcium channel blockers as well as new surgical procedures. Even the simple aspirin, taken 
every other day lowers the risk of a first heart attack.</SUM>
